-- Razgulay Says Favorable Weather Means Its Grain Crops on Target
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2013-07-03T08:41:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-03/razgulay-says-favorable-weather-means-its-grain-crops-on-target.html
OAO  Razgulay Group (GRAZ)  said good weather
means the Russian farm operator expects to meet its targets for
grain production this year.  Razgulay completed barley harvesting in the North-Caucasus
and Southern Federal Districts and reaped more than 61 percent
of winter wheat from fields in Krasnodar region. The company has
also started harvesting winter wheat in the central Belgorod
region and will begin reaping crops in the black-earth and Volga
areas this month, Razgulay said on its website yesterday.  The company operates 400,000 hectares (988,000 acres) of
land in Russia, with 240,000 hectares under crop this year
including wheat, barley,  sugar beet , rice, soya bean and
sunflower, according to company data.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
